snippet.textDisplay:
Okay so Monogon redacts the mentioning of the Void in the timeline, but in it's explanation of how it works it mentions it freely? How does that make sense? In fact, if Monogon truly discovered the void and planned to profit from it, why redact it at all? Especially if you're going to explain to everyone how it works anyways. Doesn't make sense.

If you ask me, I think Gammon actually discovered the Void (and possibly it wasn't called the void at the time). I think they figured out how dangerous it really was and shut down all experimentation on it and made the employees and developers agree to never speak about it again. BUT someone didn't listen and decided to make a profit off the void and founded Monogon. I don't think the two companies ever competed with one another during the time of duck season (80s I think?). Monogon sought to put Gammon in the hole and take credit for the discovery of the Void. This explains why on the timeline (which is supplied by Monogon themselves, so naturally it may not be 100% non-biased facts) it says "Discovery of the [REDACTED]" bc whoever founded Monogon cannot legally provide whatever name Gammon had before they renamed it the Void. It also explains how Arthur might be a double agent for Gammon. Like I said, Gammon understood the real danger that Monogon themselves didn't or simply didn't care for. They just wanted the $$. So Gammon enlists Arthur to pose as a developer and is instructed by Gammon to sneak into MythOS to shut it down and destroy it before it opens to the public and causes real havoc.

snippet.textDisplay: Fellow gamers, I think I've discovered something. If you remember playing or watching someone else play Duck Season, you'll remember that during the BadDad BadKid ending where you banish the dog with a Ouija board, a monkey doll tells you not to worry because "the "cryptid", (in this case the dog), has been banished" or whatever. But what you may not remember is that when you make yourself huge by hitting the wizard kid book with your action figure and look into what looks like a bathroom, you can see a message that reads, "Beware the monkey and cat tricksters, greater dangers await you beyond this world, I will contact you again in the next game, look for my mark", which appears as an X-like symbol on your screen. The monkey trickster is obviously the monkey doll who tells you that the dog has been banished, who we now know was lying, and the "next game" is probably referring to Boneworks. Not sure if this even matters or if it has already been discovered, but hope it helps.
